Package data.generators

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DataGenerator
    This interface defines the methods for generating data based on some underlying models.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BasicGaussianDatasetExtender
    This class finds the mean and standard deviation for each float feature in each class and makes a standardized Gaussian generator which is used to generate synthetic DataInstance objects.
    GaussianMislabeledDataGenerator
    This class generates a certain number of mislabeled data instances according to the underlying model.
    MixtureOfFloatGenerators
    This class is a meta-generator that acts as a mix of different underlying data generators in one.
    MultiDimensionalSphericGaussianGenerator
    Generate a spheric multi-dimensional Gaussian synthetic data set.
    NoisyGaussianMix
    This class generates a noisy Gaussian mix of points where Gaussian distributions are places in a region of uniform noise.
    PairedSphericGaussians
    The idea for this class was to have a generator capable of generating clusters of points that would not be entirely spherical.
    UniformGenerator
    Generates new synthetic data instances according to a uniform model.
